when shopping for a walker what type of things should i be looking for what age is appropiate to buy a walker for baby the american academy of pediatrics recommends against using walkers not only because they can discourage your child from learning to walk on their own but also because they can be dangerous so many babies end up in emergency rooms and doctor's offices from falling down stairs or bumping into furniture while in a walker if you really want one get one that has stair fall protection either a gripping mechanism that keeps the walker from going over the edge of a stairwell or a design that prevents the walker from fitting through a doorway keep in mind that some manufacturers continue to ignore these standards so do your homework good luck Stairway Breastfeeding Climbing equipment Screw Baby transport Basement Tire Humphrey Bogart Animal Crossing Glossary of climbing terms Anchor Upholstery Medicine M16 (rifle) Theory of conduct 2000 Australian Grand Prix Switch Eastern Illinois University Pediatrics M60 machine gun Domestic AC power plugs and sockets Elevator Knife Timecop Door Shaggy dog story Glossary of firefighting terms Glossary of firefighting equipment Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Charles Goodyear Spanking School bus Amulet Merchant Taylors' School General practitioner Hiking Kimberly-Clark Corporation Dalek variants Diving Phimosis Rose (Doctor Who) Androgen insensitivity syndrome Diving cylinder Bioethics of neonatal circumcision Ethical consumerism Walker tariff American Academy of Pediatrics Heinkel He 100 Growth hormone treatment Washington Monument Childbirth Bicycle helmet BS 1363 Road safety Spark plug Strap-on dildo Passenger car Dalek Professional wrestling throws Milton H. Erickson $ale of the Century Equine conformation Mountain bike Drowning Comanche Circumcision advocacy Codename: Kids Next Door Table saw Air-raid shelter Days of our Lives Johnny Belinda (1948 film) Fire exit Motorcycle Swastika Jet engine Advertising Digital rights 